Role Summary
Performs a variety of operational work in the development, installation, and maintenance of the OFC transmission and distribution network

Duties and Responsibilities
· Successfully handle all assigned fiber optic O&M work and meet the needs of customers;
· Troubleshoot and negotiate customer issues and complaints;
· Fiber optic cable laying both in backbone and access network;
· Schedule fiber cable laying and repairing project and ensure the completion within estimating cost and time;
· Optical fiber cable deploying, blowing, splicing and testing;
· Experienced by using below tools are required;
§ OTDR
§ Splicing Machine
§ Laser Source
§ Power Meter
§ Light Source (VFL)
§ Cable Locator
§ OFC Media Tester
· Delegate the tasks efficiently within the team so as to meet SLAs well within the time limits;
· Performing OFC site survey;
· Coordination with right of way (ROW)Authorities to obtain Permission and prevent fiber cuts;
· Having good relationship with the customers;
· Have a positive attitude in carrying out his duties for AFTEL;
· Attend meeting when required;
· Effectively prioritize and execute tasks in a high-pressure environment;
· Executing any other tasks assign by line manager;

Job Requirements
Education: Degree in Telecommunication/ Electronics/ Computer science / Information Technology or related field.
Experience: Minimum of two years for bachelor degree holder. and one year for Master degree holder.
Skills Required:
· Having DSL, ADSL, VDSL, IMS services & Fixed-Line Net concept and knowledge;
· CCN access equipment configuration and troubleshooting skills
· Hand on experience in CCN network troubleshooting.
· Able to travel and work throughout the country, including remote locations
· Candidates with no prior experience are also welcome to apply;
· Knowledge and experience in any of the following areas has an advantage:
o IP network
o CCNA Certified
· Willing to work on Standby duties, tight timelines and to be ready to carry out 24x7 facility on-call responsibility;
· Willing to perform shift duty if required;
· Ability of reading, speaking and writing of Dari, Pashto and English Languages

Submission Guidelines
متقاضیان میتوانند cv یا خلص صوانح شانرا به ایمیل آدرس های hr@afghantelecom.af با ذکر نمبر بست (OFC-010) و عنوان بست درموضوع ایمیل ارسال نمایند. متقاضیانیکه درخواستی خویش را بعد از تاریخ اعلان بست ارسال مینمایند و یا هم شرایط مندرج این بست را تکمیل ننمایند شامل پروسه امتحان تحریری و مصاحبه نمیگردند.
